text.text: I am shocked to see such low rating for this Walgreens, located on Pine & Montgomery. I had THE BEST experience today--I am sick with SOMETHING and you know how nowadays the worry is that it's COVID. So I was asking someone at the pharmacy what the word "Antigen" meant and instead of just answering my question and letting me browse endlessly, the lady says "Let's see if that test is covered by your insurance". Nobody ever offered to check that for me anywhere!! She (her name is Jonelyn) recommended a better brand of test and it was covered by insurance, so instead of $23 I probably paid $4. As she was ringing me up, she says "You should think of getting your flu shot. Come back when you have more time, we can do it on your lunch break".  Have you ever had such a customer service anywhere? I haven't. In my state of concern whether I got COVID, I wasn't even thinking of how to save money or prevent future illness, but somebody at Walgreens was! I am switching my prescriptions to THIS pharmacy! Thank you so much for having such fantastic employees!

editorialSummary.text: Snug family-owned convenience store with a few seats for coffee & sandwiches, plus snacks.

text.text:
This place is great!  Don't get me wrong, it's a smaller shop, but the prices are way better than Woodlands Market down the street.

The sandwiches at the Deli are great, my wife and I find them to be big enough to share if we get a snack on the side as well.

You'll find alcohol, cleaning supplies, cooking/baking supplies, milk, eggs, small pharmacy, canned foods, etc.  There's no salad bar nor a produce section, though I would say this place doesn't really look to say that it has these things.

Lastly, if you talk to the family that runs the place you'll realize that it is a really comfortable place to be.  Very kind people here.

Ultimately, this place isn't a grocery store, it's a market, and in my opinion it is a very good one.
